<TEXT>
the most rev robert runcie said sunday he will 
retire next january as archbishop of canterbury the leader of 70 
million anglicans worldwide 
runcie made the announcement during a morning service at 
canterbury cathedral marking the 10th anniversary of his 
enthronement his london office said 
runcie offered his resignation to queen elizabeth ii in her role 
as head of the church of england one of 27 selfgoverning churches 
within the anglican communion which also includes 25 million us 
episcopalians 
the church of england requires its bishops to retire at age 70 
but runcie said he would step down on january 31 eight months 
before his 70th birthday on oct 2 1991 
the gap leaves time for prime minister margaret thatcher to 
appoint his successor it is widely believed she will select 
someone whose social and economic views are more in tune with her 
own 
runcie a liberal prelate has often spoken against the policies 
of mrs thatchers governing conservative party 
he preached forgiveness after britains victory over argentina 
in the 1982 falklands war he supported coal miners during their 
1984 strike and in 1985 runcie said the english church should 
contribute millions of dollars to relieve poverty and homelessness 
in britain 
i judge the beginning of 1991 to be the right time for me to 
hand over to the next archbishbop of canterbury runcie said in a 
statement 
the public announcement today will give sufficient time for 
the name of my successor to be known well before the end of this 
year i ask for prayers in support of those responsible for making 
that choice 
runcie has been credited with holding his church together during 
controversy over the ordination of women bishops about 1200 women 
priests have been ordained by us episcopalians and anglicans in 
canada and new zealand but the church of england still does not 
permit the ordination of women 
runcies personal envoy terry waite is among 18 westerners 
held hostage in lebanon the longestheld is terry anderson chief 
middle east correspondent of the associated press kidnapped march 
16 1985 waite was trying to negotiate the release of other 
hostages when he disappeared in beirut in january 1987 
</TEXT>
