<TEXT>
saloth suong devoted his life to 
cambodian buddhism and royal tradition his brother tried to 
eradicate both and stands accused of slaughtering 33 million 
compatriots 
saloth suongs brother is saloth sar alias pol pot whose 
primitive communist revolution ranks in savagery with adolf 
hitlers holocaust and the mass purges of soviet dictator josef 
stalin 
saloth suong 78 says he is unsure what drove his younger 
brother to impose the reign of terror whose victims included 
members of their own family 
he does not want to see his brother again either for a personal 
reunion or as head of the khmer rouge guerrillas pol pot is said to 
still lead 
but i am not afraid if they come i am too old already for 
fear he said i pray often at the pagoda 
his 71yearold wife chea samy is less fatalistic the most 
prominent mistress of cambodian classical dance she works to 
preserve the art as a teacher at the fine arts university 
in one of the many tragic ironies of the couples lives it was 
pol pot who tried to stamp out the exquisite dance along with 
other centuriesold cultural legacies 
if they came back they would destroy it again so i must teach 
and document as much as possible she said sitting beside her 
husband in their spartan rooms in a decrepit apartment block 
saloth suong bears a striking resemblance to his infamous 
brother he has the same stocky build fleshy cheeks and high 
forehead and he says the two were close as boys and young men 
saloth sar was a very polite gentle boy he respected the old 
people and they liked him his brother said i have no idea why 
he became so evil i keep wondering about that maybe it was the 
things he studied and the friends who influenced him 
pol pots father is said to have been a landowning farmer of 
good standing a cousin who married into the royal family took some 
of the nine children including pol pot and saloth suong to phnom 
penh for studies 
through the cousin pol pot is distantly related to prince 
norodom sihanouk the former cambodian leader imprisoned by pol pot 
and now chief of the uneasy guerrilla alliance fighting phnom 
penhs vietnamesebacked government the usbacked resistance 
includes the khmer rouge 
saloth suong says pol pot lived with him for years chea samy 
bought him food washed his clothes and helped him with life in the 
capital the cousin connected to the cambodian royalty proved a 
second mother 
with a scholarship in hand pol pot left to study radio 
electronics in paris in 1949 but failed his exams much of his time 
