he would soon dominate for years saloth suong thought his brother 
had been killed 
saloth suongs own career was spent within the royal palace as 
an administrator protocol official and personal assistant to 
sihanouks mother queen kossamak 
sihanouk was toppled in 1970 and the ensuing fiveyear war ended 
with a khmer rouge victory saloth suong a brother and sister were 
forced into agrarian communes along with the entire population 
the brother died of hunger and illness and pol pots second 
mother starved to death 
saloth suong and chea samy say they labored from 5 am to 7 
pm he cut logs for firewood she washed 700 dishes daily in a 
communal kitchen illness sapped their strength 
in late 1978 while cleaning the communal kitchen saloth sar 
watched workers putting up a photograph of the shadowy khmer rouge 
leader who had discarded his real name for that of pol pot 
at first i didnt recognize him but some people noted the 
resemblance and told me that pol pot was saloth sar he said 
recalling his feeling of anger 
people asked me why dont you go to pol pot he is a big 
man but i told them he was not really a brother to me so i could 
not come to him 
vietnamese forces overthrew the khmer rouge in late 1978 the 
government has said the regime killed 33 million people in 
executions famine and civil unrest other estimates are lower but 
still astounding given cambodias 1975 population of about 8 
million 
after the new government was installed in early 1979 saloth 
suong and his wife returned to phnom penh and his brother fled back 
to the jungle despite his announced retirement in 1985 pol pot is 
believed to still lead the khmer rouge 
vietnam said it withdrew all its troops from cambodia last year 
leaving the government led by prime minister hun sen to fight the 
resistance 
saloth suong lives quietly and works parttime as a keeper of 
artistic property at the ministry of culture late last year he 
returned to his native village for a reunion with three surviving 
siblings there was a buddhist ceremony of gratitude and 
remembrance of dead family members 
the village temple traditional center of rural life had been 
turned into a hospital by the khmer rouge its images smashed its 
monks derobed asked if they were shunned because of their brother 
saloth suong laughed gently 
not at all he said the villagers welcomed us with warmth 
because they knew we too had suffered under pol pot 
