limited relations with syria in view of egypts close ties with 
iraq syrias archrival in the arab world 
a meeting between assad and mubarak after decembers resumption 
of diplomatic ties was originally expected to take place in syria 
there were several syrian reports of an imminent damascus meeting 
but mubarak never showed up perhaps unwilling to be seen as 
knocking on assads door perhaps fearing resentment by iraq 
diplomats in damascus said the egyptian president would like to 
act as a matchmaker between assad and iraqi president saddam 
hussein but given the deep hostility between two of the arab 
worlds most ruthless and ambitious leaders there were no signs 
that there will be an opportunity for reconciliation 
intensifying the feud between the iraqi and syrian wings of the 
arab baath socialist party ruling in both countries baghdad has 
supplied weapons to lebanons antisyrian christian leader gen 
michel aoun thwarting assads effort to impose a pax syriana on 
its wartorn neighbor 
syria was the only major arab country to side with persian iran 
in its war against arab iraq 
